[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dyfed-Powys boss suspended over payments to husband's firm

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Dyfed-Powys Police's director of legal services has been suspended over payments made to a firm of barristers where her husband worked.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Independent Police Complaints Commission said Samantha Gainard had signed off invoices for legal services "over a number of years".
The police watchdog is looking into her role in instructing the company.
It is also investigating whether she declared a potential conflict of interest.
A separate investigation is looking into her relationship with the force's deputy chief constable Carl Langley.
